This web application is a tool to visualize degrees at York University. An informed decision can be made by viewing pre-requisites and co-requisites to determine the most efficient path with least amount of classes taken to graduate.

Grad Map with Node and SQL

app.post('/', function(req, res) {
    var queryProgram = req.body.option1;

    var sql = "";
    var yearArray = [];

    if (req.body.option2 == 3) {
        // console.log("????????????????????????", req.body.option2);
        sql = " DROP VIEW IF EXISTS `lassonde`.`v1` cascade ; CREATE VIEW `lassonde`.`v1` AS SELECT `lassonde`.`group_courses`.`cNum` AS `name` FROM ((`lassonde`.`group_courses` JOIN `lassonde`.`program_course_groups`) JOIN `lassonde`.`program` ON (((`lassonde`.`program`.`pNum` = "+queryProgram+") AND (`lassonde`.`program_course_groups`.`pNum` = `lassonde`.`program`.`pNum`) AND (`lassonde`.`program_course_groups`.`gNum` = `lassonde`.`group_courses`.`gNum`)))); SELECT v7.course as name, numberofTimes, course.cYear FROM `lassonde`.`v7`, course WHERE v7.course = course.cNum and course.cYear = ?;SELECT v7.course as name, numberofTimes, course.cYear FROM lassonde.v7, course WHERE v7.course = course.cNum and course.cYear = ?;SELECT v7.course as name, numberofTimes, course.cYear FROM `lassonde`.`v7`, course WHERE v7.course = course.cNum and course.cYear = ?; SELECT * FROM v3;";
        yearArray.push(1,2,3);
    }
    else {
        sql = " DROP VIEW IF EXISTS `lassonde`.`v1` cascade ; CREATE VIEW `lassonde`.`v1` AS SELECT `lassonde`.`group_courses`.`cNum` AS `name` FROM ((`lassonde`.`group_courses` JOIN `lassonde`.`program_course_groups`) JOIN `lassonde`.`program` ON (((`lassonde`.`program`.`pNum` = "+queryProgram+") AND (`lassonde`.`program_course_groups`.`pNum` = `lassonde`.`program`.`pNum`) AND (`lassonde`.`program_course_groups`.`gNum` = `lassonde`.`group_courses`.`gNum`)))); SELECT v7.course as name, numberofTimes, course.cYear FROM `lassonde`.`v7`, course WHERE v7.course = course.cNum and course.cYear = ?;SELECT v7.course as name, numberofTimes, course.cYear FROM lassonde.v7, course WHERE v7.course = course.cNum and course.cYear = ?;SELECT v7.course as name, numberofTimes, course.cYear FROM `lassonde`.`v7`, course WHERE v7.course = course.cNum and course.cYear = ?;  SELECT v7.course as name, numberofTimes, course.cYear FROM `lassonde`.`v7`, course WHERE v7.course = course.cNum and course.cYear = ?;   SELECT * FROM v3;";
        // console.log("re################q",req.body.option1, req.body.option2);

        yearArray.push(1,2,3,4);

    }
    let obj = [];
    let obj1 = [];
    let obj2 = [];
    let obj3 = [];
    let obj4 = [];
    let arrofNodes = [];
    let links = [];
    let maxArr = [];
    connection.query(sql, yearArray, function(error, results, fields) { //is it iterated multiple times or just once???

        if (error) {
            throw error;
        }
        for (let index = 2; index < results.length - 1; index++) {
            // console.log("indexs", index);
            obj.push(order(results[index]));
        }
        let flashCounter = 0
        for (let outerIndex = 0; outerIndex < obj.length; outerIndex++) {
            for (let innerIndex = 0; innerIndex < obj[outerIndex].length; innerIndex++) {
                arrofNodes[flashCounter] = obj[outerIndex][innerIndex];
                flashCounter++;
            }
        }
        // console.log("arrofNodesarrofNodes",arrofNodes);
        
        links = results[results.length-1]  //prereq table


        let globalLinks = [];
        var glink = {
            source: 0,
            target: 0
        };
        for (let index = 0; index < links.length; index++) {
            links[index].source = getSourceIndex(links[index].name);
            links[index].target = getTargetIndex(links[index].prerequisites);
        }

        function getSourceIndex(d) {
            for (let index = 0; index < arrofNodes.length; index++) {
                if (d === arrofNodes[index].name) {
                    return arrofNodes[index];
                }
            }
        };

        function getTargetIndex(d) {
            for (let index = 0; index < arrofNodes.length; index++) {
                if (d === arrofNodes[index].name) {
                    // console.log(index);
                    return arrofNodes[index];
                }
            }
        };
        //generates an array of no of courses in each year


        var arrayLength = [];
        for (let i = 2; i < results.length; i++) {
            // console.log("arrayleng",arrayLength);
            arrayLength.push(results[i].length);
        }
        var graph = {
            "nodes": arrofNodes,
            "links": links,
            "arrayLength": arrayLength
        };
        // console.log("graph :::",graph);
        
        res.send(graph); // loop back the json object

    });
}); 

function order(megaOBJ) {
    var desc = megaOBJ.sort((a, b) => b.numberofTimes - a.numberofTimes); //desc order on nooftimes
    var mid = Math.floor(megaOBJ.length / 2);
    var len = megaOBJ.length;
    let temp = new Array(len);
    var tempL = []
    var tempR = []
    temp[mid] = desc[0];
    for (let index = 1; index < len; index += 2) {
        tempL.push(desc[index]);
    }
    for (let index = 2; index < len; index += 2) {
        tempR.push(desc[index]);
    }
    for (let index = 0; index < tempR.length; index++) {
        temp[mid + index + 1] = tempR[index];
    }
    for (let index = 0; index < tempL.length; index++) {
        temp[mid - index - 1] = tempL[index];
    }
    //final
    for (let index = 0; index < temp.length; index++) {
        temp[index].cx = index + 1;
        temp[index].cy = temp[index].cYear;
    }

    
    return temp;
};

                (nodes[link.source] = { name: link.source });
            link.target = nodes[link.target] ||

        });
            
           


       
        // add svg(scalable vector graphics) to DOM body, this is like a canvas nd allows us to manipulate graphics
        var svg = d3.select('body').append('svg')
            .attr('width', width)

        // force layout is a physics-based simulator that allows us to apply 'forces' between elements
        var force = d3.layout.force()
            .size([width, height])

            .links(links)
            .charge(-400)
            //on any action on the force layout
            .on("tick", tick)

            //add a class = link to all links

                .call(force.drag);

CREATE VIEW `computerSecurity`.`v1` AS
    SELECT 
        `computerSecurity`.`COURSE`.`cNum` AS `name`
    FROM
        `computerSecurity`.`COURSE`
    WHERE
        (`computerSecurity`.`COURSE`.`cYear` = 2)
;

CREATE VIEW `computerSecurity`.`v2` AS
    SELECT 
        `computerSecurity`.`COURSE`.`cNum` AS `name`,
        `computerSecurity`.`COURSE_PREQ_GROUPS`.`preqGroupNum` AS `preqGroupNum`
    FROM
        (`computerSecurity`.`COURSE`
        JOIN `computerSecurity`.`COURSE_PREQ_GROUPS` ON ((`computerSecurity`.`COURSE`.`cNum` = `computerSecurity`.`COURSE_PREQ_GROUPS`.`cNum`)))

;

CREATE VIEW `computerSecurity`.`v3` AS
    SELECT 
        `v2`.`name` AS `name`,
        `computerSecurity`.`PREQ_GROUP_COURSES`.`cNum` AS `prerequisites`
    FROM
        (`computerSecurity`.`v2`
        JOIN `computerSecurity`.`PREQ_GROUP_COURSES` ON ((`v2`.`preqGroupNum` = `computerSecurity`.`PREQ_GROUP_COURSES`.`preqGroupNum`)))

;

CREATE VIEW `computerSecurity`.`v4` AS
    SELECT 
        `computerSecurity`.`PREQ_GROUP_COURSES`.`cNum` AS `COURSE`,
        COUNT(0) AS `numberOfTimes`
    FROM
        `computerSecurity`.`PREQ_GROUP_COURSES`
    GROUP BY `computerSecurity`.`PREQ_GROUP_COURSES`.`cNum`
    ORDER BY `numberOfTimes` DESC

;

CREATE VIEW `computerSecurity`.`v5` AS
    SELECT 
        `C`.`cNum` AS `COURSE`, 0 AS `numberofTimes`
    FROM
        `computerSecurity`.`COURSE` `C`
    WHERE
        (NOT (`C`.`cNum` IN (SELECT 
                `v4`.`COURSE`
            FROM
                `computerSecurity`.`v4`)))
;

CREATE VIEW `computerSecurity`.`v6` AS
    SELECT 
        `v4`.`COURSE` AS `course`,
        `v4`.`numberOfTimes` AS `numberOfTimes`
    FROM
        `computerSecurity`.`v4` 
    UNION SELECT 
        `v5`.`COURSE` AS `course`,
        `v5`.`numberofTimes` AS `numberofTimes`
    FROM
        `computerSecurity`.`v5`
;



CREATE VIEW `computerSecurity`.`v7` AS
    SELECT 
        `v6`.`course` AS `course`,
        `v6`.`numberOfTimes` AS `numberofTimes`
    FROM
        `computerSecurity`.`v6`
    ORDER BY `v6`.`numberOfTimes` DESC
;


CREATE VIEW `computerSecurity`.`v8` AS
    SELECT 
        `v7`.`course` AS `name`,
        `v7`.`numberofTimes` AS `numberofTimes`,
        `computerSecurity`.`COURSE`.`cYear` AS `cYear`
    FROM
        (`computerSecurity`.`v7`
        JOIN `computerSecurity`.`COURSE`)
    WHERE
        (`v7`.`course` = `computerSecurity`.`COURSE`.`cNum`)
;
